Conditional logic
Can I use if / else statements like in NONMEM or nlmixr2?
Yes. Two forms are supported in [individual_parameters] and [odes]:
# Block form
if (WT &gt; 70) {
  CL = TVCL * (WT / 70)^0.75 * exp(ETA_CL)
} else if (SEX == 1) {
  CL = TVCL * 1.2 * exp(ETA_CL)
} else {
  CL = TVCL * exp(ETA_CL)
}

# Inline (ternary) form
CL = if (SEX == 1) TVCL * 1.5 else TVCL
Compared to NONMEM: C-style {braces} and operators (&gt;, ==, &&) rather than Fortran-style IF THEN … ENDIF and .GT., .LE., etc.
Compared to nlmixr2: near-verbatim match — replace &lt;- with =.
Caveat: == and != do bitwise float comparison. They work for integer-coded covariates (SEX == 1) but are unreliable for continuous thresholds. Prefer WT &gt;= 70 && WT &lt; 80 over WT == 75.
Caveat: when a parameter is assigned inside an if block, mu-reference detection is skipped for that parameter. See Individual Parameters.
